# The `throws` Keyword

If you write a function that is dangerous (e.g., it connects to the internet), you MUST place a warning label on it.

We do this by adding the `throws` keyword right before the return arrow `->`.

```swift
func login(pin: Int) throws -> String {
    // Function body goes here
}
```
This explicitly warns any developer using this function: "Hey! This function might fail, so you better be prepared!"

# Halting Execution

Inside the risky function, if we detect that something went terribly wrong, we instantly halt the function by using the `throw` keyword, followed by the specific Error from our Enum.

```swift
func processPayment(amount: Int) throws {
    if amount > 5000 {
        // Instantly stops the function and throws the error!
        throw BankError.insufficientFunds
    }

    print("Payment successful.")
}
```
